BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2026-03-17-1800-studiotwothree@rvafiguredrawing
DTSTAMP:20260309T131943Z
DTSTART:20260317T180000
DTEND:20260317T210000
SUMMARY:Figure Drawing Night
LOCATION:Studio Two Three\, 109 W 15th St Richmond\, VA 23224
DESCRIPTION:3-hour figure drawing workshop with a professional nude model. Instructor Carter Helmandollar will call poses — starting with short gestural poses and concluding with longer poses. Bring your own drawing/painting/sculpting materials.\\n\\nCost: $20\\n\\nRegister: https://www.studiotwothree.org/classes/p/figure-drawing-night
URL:https://www.studiotwothree.org/classes/p/figure-drawing-night
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2026-03-18-1800-artworks@rvafiguredrawing
DTSTAMP:20260309T131943Z
DTSTART:20260318T180000
DTEND:20260318T200000
SUMMARY:Queer Life Drawing
LOCATION:Gold Lion Community Cafe\, 1012 Hull Street\, Richmond\, VA 23224
DESCRIPTION:Chill vibe life drawing session celebrating queer bodies and creativity. Whether a pro or just want to doodle\, everyone's welcome. Bring your own art supplies.\\n\\nCost: Donation\\n\\nRegister: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/queer-life-drawing-tickets-1984671499882
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/queer-life-drawing-tickets-1984671499882
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2026-03-21-1000-vmfa@rvafiguredrawing
DTSTAMP:20260309T131943Z
DTSTART:20260321T100000
DTEND:20260321T160000
SUMMARY:Figure Drawing [27]
LOCATION:VMFA Studio School\, 200 N Arthur Ashe Boulevard\, Richmond\, VA 23220
DESCRIPTION:Start by exploring a variety of drawings of the human form by other artists. Then with guidance from the instructor and working from a live model\, learn to create expressive portraits in charcoal and pencil. Prerequisites: basic drawing skills. Instructor: Amy Smith. (1 session)\\n\\nCost: Member $80\\n\\nRegister: https://www.vmfa.museum/classes/figure-drawing-27
URL:https://www.vmfa.museum/classes/figure-drawing-27
END:VEVENT
